$a)$ An average rate of return on investment is calculated by dividing the average net income of the firm by the average book value of the investment.

Now, let's see the formula for average accounting return which we denote with $AAR$

$$\begin{align*}
AAR&=\frac{ANI}{ABV}
\end{align*}$$

where the average net income $ANI$ and the average book value $ABV$
